REMARKS: Four of our six vouchers were shot from trees at night by Matses hunters, three in secondary forest (abandoned swiddens) and one in hilltop primary forest; heights were not recorded, but the specimen shot in primary forest was said to be “very high up in a big tree” (English translation from Matses field notes). One specimen was captured by hand in the late afternoon by several boys, who shook it from the crown of a small guaba tree ( Fabaceae :
Inga edulis
) on the outskirts of the village. The specimen from Jenaro Herrera was trapped on a liana 18 m above the ground in disturbed primary forest.
